cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper deals with analyzing learned representations in Convolutional Neural Networks (Convnets) for computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses clustering techniques and transfer learning, which are common topics in machine learning. Hence, it is likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) categories. The paper also deals with the high dimensionality of internal representations, which is a common challenge in neural networks. Therefore, it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) category. Finally, the paper discusses the interpretation of Convnets, which is a topic in natural language processing. Hence, it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language) category.
